data.summary: [Business Wire] - NEW YORK & TOKYO--(BUSINESSWIRE)-- American International Group, Inc. (NYSE:AIG - News) today announced that it has agreed to sell its Japan life insurance business AIG Fuji Life Insurance Company, Ltd. (AFLI) to FWD Group, the insurance arm of Pacific Century Group. This transaction does not affect AIG’s extensive non-life insurance business in Japan, the largest of any foreign-based insurer in the country. AIG will continue to focus on Japan’s property and casualty (P&C) market through its local subsidiaries Fuji Fire & Marine, Ltd., AIU Insurance Company, Ltd., and American Home Assurance Company, Ltd. These companies provide commercial insurance and services, as well as personal insurance coverage lines, including accident & health, auto, homeowners, and travel insurance.
